parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower ball joint can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries. It can also cause the wheel to detach from the vehicle, resulting in loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The front lower ball joint fractures
causing a loud popping and clunking noise when turning at low speeds
the vehicle shakes violently
the wheel detaches from the vehicle
and the vehicle lowers onto the tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the rear lower control arm can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries. It can also cause the vehicle to shake or vibrate, making it difficult to control.
symptoms: The rear lower control arm corrodes
causing the vehicle to shake or vibrate
and the vehicle loses control when turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the suspension can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries. It can also cause the vehicle to shake or vibrate, making it difficult to control.
symptoms: The suspension fails
causing the vehicle to shake or vibrate
and the vehicle loses control when turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of parts for recall repairs can cause the vehicle to remain in an unsafe condition, leading to potential accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The parts for recall repairs are not available
and the dealer or manufacturer is unable to provide a timeline for when the parts will be available.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window regulator can cause the window to fall down into the door, making it difficult or impossible to close, which can lead to safety hazards, such as weather damage, theft, and accidents.
symptoms: The window falls down into the door
the window does not roll up or down
the window regulator makes a loud noise
the window cable breaks
the window motor fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank straps can cause the fuel tank to shift or fall, leading to fuel leakage and potentially causing a fire in the event of a crash, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Fuel tank straps are broken or damaged
fuel tank is lying on the ground
fuel leakage
difficulty fueling the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to repair the trailer hitch can cause the fuel tank to shift or fall, leading to fuel leakage and potentially causing a fire in the event of a crash, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Difficulty scheduling a repair appointment
lack of available parts
corrosion issues preventing repair
dealership refusing to perform repair.
